Specify queue

To specify a queue for the `correct_data` periodic task, you can modify the `add_periodic_task` call to include the `queue` parameter like this:

```python
sender.add_periodic_task(
    crontab(hour="6", minute="15"),
    correct_data.s(),
    queue='data_correction'  # Specify your desired queue name here
)
```

This will make the `correct_data` task run on the specified queue ('data_correction' in this example). Workers listening to this queue will pick up and process these tasks.

This is useful for:
- Load balancing across different workers
- Prioritizing different types of tasks
- Segregating resource-intensive operations
- Ensuring certain tasks run on specific workers with the required capabilities

Make sure you have workers configured to consume from this queue by starting them with the `-Q data_correction` option or by configuring the queue in your Celery worker settings.
